ted for AGN at comparable luminosities from multi-wavelength surveys\n(0.1-0.3). Assuming random nuclear orientation, the unobscured half-opening\nangle of the disk/wind/torus structure is ~ 60deg and the obscuring material\ncovers 30deg of which ~ 12deg is Compton thick. The multi-wavelength properties\nreveal that many NLRGs have intrinsic absorption 10-1000x higher than indicated\nby their X-ray hardness ratios, and their true L_X values are ~10--100x larger\nthan the hardness-ratio absorption corrections would indicate.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 4 Jun 2013 16:59:35 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-16"}
