ss a wide range of galaxy mass. Gravitational\nlensing and dynamical perturbations of tidal streams in the stellar halo\nprovide evidence for an abundant population of low mass subhalos in accord with\nCDM predictions. These observational approaches will get more powerful over the\nnext few years.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 4 Jun 2013 20:03:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-09-07"}
